You can solve this by using [FocusScope](https://api.flutter.dev/flutter/widgets/FocusScope-class.html).
In your sample code, the reason focus was moved from the `GestureDetector` to `RawMaterialButton` because the scope is global. Meaning, if there is a potential focus node in the direction of key press, focus is shifted there, else it stays in the same widget.

